description: The Government of Canada spent an estimated $320.1M
  in 2021-2022 on contracts with CANADIAN CORPS OF COMMISSIONAIRES. The average
  contract duration was 0.82 year, and the average contract
  value (not including contracts under $10k) was $290.3K.
  The longest contract was 8.01 year. The largest contract
  by value (including amendments) was $13.5M.
